no sarcasam at all. this is really smart. and its the source of a lot of not only the webs problems but the worlds problems. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 380<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 6:36:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I think the point ..</span><hr size=1> .. of the RP versus non-RP debate is not that non-RP'ers are hostile to RP.  They're manifestly not.  Most seem to like it.  I never had a single problem with it on nomal blue nor even heard of one.  There was a strong minority there that RP'd a fair bit.  I had friends tell me they missed my RP-character when I stopped playing him for my monk -- dunno if I should take that as a compliment or insult.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
No, the point of it is that for some, RP is intensely immersive.  Having someone /shout &quot;ur ghey, my uberness ownz joo!&quot; or variations on that disrupts their immersion even when the d00d is just shouting it in fun to his buddy across the zone.  RP'ers in EQ are looking for a server with a culture more supportive of immersion, where it's easier to get in-character and stay in-character.  I think FV has that.<br>
<br>
IMHO, Verant only did two things to support RP on FV.  They marked the server RP-preferred.  They made languages useful.  The languages are big boost to getting IC.  The /shout and /ooc changes don't help -- you could always turn them off.  The TLC, 1-char, and no no-drops all have different effects other than RP-support, too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crime Lord</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 6:43:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I think the point ..</span><hr size=1> Yeah, but there's still Lore, which I'll never understand how it fits into roleplaying.<br>
